    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="304"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3454</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCAdR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="9" xml:id="d304fn9">Transmitted to the Commission to Negotiate Peace in
                        Department’s telegram No. 497, Jan. 30, 1919, 4 p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 55</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Chargé d’Affaires presents his compliments to the Acting Secretary
                    of State and has the honour to inform him, by direction of His Majesty’s
                    Government and with reference to the memorandum from this Embassy No. 43 of
                    January 15th, that His Majesty’s Government have received a telegram from the
                    British High Commissioner in Siberia stating that the Omsk Government have heard
                    that Monsieur Sazonoff is going to Paris and that they have expressed the hope
                    that he will act as their Agent and as the agent of the other new Governments in
                    Russia as well as of Deniken.</p>
                <p>The British High Commissioner has requested the Foreign Office to cause the wish
                    of the Omsk Government to be conveyed to Monsieur Sazonoff.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-20">January 20,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
